[Amit Varma]: Please welcome your host, Amit Bharma.

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:07.880
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Scene and the Unseen.

00:01:07.880 --> 00:01:12.240
[Amit Varma]: If modern Indian politics has been taken over by the jugalbandi of Narendra Modi and Amit

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:17.880
[Amit Varma]: Shah, this pair of politicians was enabled by an earlier jugalbandi before them, that

00:01:17.880 --> 00:01:20.760
[Amit Varma]: of Atal Bihari Vajpayee and Lal Krishna Advani.

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:25.640
[Amit Varma]: For decades, Vajpayee and Advani fought what appeared to be a losing battle until they

00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:26.640
[Amit Varma]: won.

00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:30.840
[Amit Varma]: No matter which side of the political spectrum you're on, this is a fascinating story.

00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:35.840
[Amit Varma]: To understand India, we have to understand the rise of Hindu nationalism and the rise

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:37.200
[Amit Varma]: of the BJP.

00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:42.840
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is Vinay Sitapati, author of the marvelous book, Jugalbandi, the BJP before

00:01:42.840 --> 00:01:43.840
[Amit Varma]: Modi.

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:47.160
[Amit Varma]: Vinay has been a lawyer, a journalist, and a political scientist.

00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:52.840
[Amit Varma]: And when you read his book, you'll find that he's a fine historian and writer as well.

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:57.760
[Amit Varma]: Jugalbandi looks at the evolution of political Hindu nationalism through the prism of the

00:01:57.760 --> 00:02:03.380
[Amit Varma]: partnership between Vajpayee and Advani, a friendship that spanned decades and was even

00:02:03.380 --> 00:02:05.360
[Amit Varma]: a bit of a bromance, actually.

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:10.680
[Amit Varma]: The book busts the simple stereotypes that linger around both men and gave me great insight

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:16.660
[Amit Varma]: into the RSS, the motivations of Hindu nationalism, and how this was a bottom-up movement in which

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:22.720
[Amit Varma]: the politicians were merely rational actors responding to incentives from the demand side

00:02:22.720 --> 00:02:24.880
[Amit Varma]: of the political marketplace.

00:02:24.880 --> 00:02:29.040
[Amit Varma]: And that remains the case even in this age of Modi and Shah.

